main event: Airmen reported several white lights moving in various directions in the Pacific Ocean area.
interesting points: The sighting was reported to a USAF base.
The report mentions an unidentified flying object with a steady white light, suspected to be a satellite.
The object appeared from the south at a high altitude of 29 degrees, traveled rapidly, and disappeared at an altitude of 19 degrees.
The object was tracked for approximately 10 minutes from 1730Z to 1740Z.
The report was received by telcon from ROA radio.
sighted object: several white lights moving in various directions
